=Courtesan Culture=
==Literature==
===PhD Dissertations===
* Stephen H. Cheng: Flowers of Shanghai and the Late Ch'ing Courtesan Novels. Harvard University. 1979
* Alexander Des Forges: Street Talk and Alley Stories: Tangled Narratives of Shanghai from Lives of Shanghai Flowers (1892) to Midnight (1933). University of Princeton, 1998
* [[Chloë F. Starr]]: The Late Qing Courtesan Novel as Text and Fiction. University of Oxford, 1999
* [[Paola Zamperini]]: Lost Bodies: Images and Representations of Prostitution in Late Qing Fiction. University of California at Berkeley, 1999
===Monographs===
* [[Christian Henriot]]: Belles de Shanghai. Prostitution et sexualité en Chine aux XIXe-XXe siècles, Paris, Editions du CNRS, 1997
* [[Matthew Sommer]]: Sex, Law and Society in Late Imperial China. Stanford: Stanford University Press, 2000
* [[Christian Henriot]]: Prostitution and Sexuality in Shanghai: A Social History 1849-1949. Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, 2001
* [[Catherine Yeh]]: Shanghai Love: Courtesans, Intellectuals and Entertainment Culture 1850-1910. Washington: University of Washington Press, 2006
* [[Chloë F. Starr]]: Red-light Novels of the late Qing. Leiden: Brill, 2007